Wash and dry produce. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}.

Open package of shrimp and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1/2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} (large pan for 4 servings) over
medium-high heat. Add @shrimp{10%ounce} in a single layer; season with
@dried thyme{1%tsp}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp} (all for 4), @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is browned,
~{1-2%minutes} (it'll finish cooking later in this step).

Add garlic and @Israeli couscous{5%ounce}; cook, stirring, until garlic is
fragrant and couscous is toasted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and
a pinch of @salt{}. Cover and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce heat to
low and cook until couscous is tender and water has absorbed,
~{12-14%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Swap in
shrimp for chicken.

== Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly
chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add green beans and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{3-6%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Sprinkle couscous with juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4
servings) and garnish with parsley.

> TIP: For less lemon flavor, use one wedge for 2 servings and two wedges
> for 4.

Divide couscous between shallow #bowls{} or serve directly from pan. Serve
with green beans and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.